dct_description_sm: Printed with vegetation. Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (GE), Corps of Engineers, U. S. Army , original map compiled by photogrammetric methods by U. S. Geological Survey. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Mount Carmel, Indiana : Franklin County. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 4062 IV NW. Edition 1--AMS 1. Transverse Mercator projection. "Series V851" Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, buildings, and natural features. "Contour interval 10 feet." Marginal maps: Index to boundaries.--Index to adjoining sheets. "Copied in 1956 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Mount Carmel, 1956. Original map compiled by photogrammetric methods by the U. S. Geological Survey from aerial photographs taken 1954. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS, and Indiana Flood Control and Water Resources Commission. ... Map field checked, 1955. Scale changed, Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, and marginal data revised, 1957." "Edition 1--AMS (First printing, 1-58)." "Printed by Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, 1-58."
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, [1958].
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); United States. Army Map Service
